### `pluto_client.py` self-test

The Python client includes a self-test entry point that verifies the client library
itself against a live server:

```bash
python3 pluto_client.py selftest --host localhost --port 9000
```

Output:
```
[PASS] connect and register
[PASS] ping / pong
[PASS] acquire lock
[PASS] lock conflict (waiter)
[PASS] release lock
[PASS] lock_granted event received
[PASS] direct message
[PASS] broadcast
[PASS] list_agents
[PASS] event_history query
[PASS] deadlock detection
[PASS] disconnect

All 12 checks passed in 0.41s
```

The Python self-test uses two `PlutoClient` instances in separate threads to
simulate two concurrent agents, just as the scenario tests do.

