## Part 4 — Test Scenario Runner (`tests/run_scenarios.py`)

The scenario runner is a standalone Python script that discovers and runs
scenario modules in `tests/scenarios/`.

```
tests/
├── run_scenarios.py          # discovery and runner
└── scenarios/
    ├── s01_shared_file.py
    ├── s02_port_reservation.py
    ├── s03_pipeline_handoff.py
    ├── s04_deadlock_recovery.py
    ├── s05_broadcast.py
    ├── s06_reconnect.py
    ├── s07_concurrent_readers.py
    ├── s08_fencing_token.py
    ├── s09_max_wait.py
    └── s10_stress.py
```

Each scenario module exposes a single function:

```python
def run(host: str, port: int) -> tuple[bool, str]:
    """Returns (passed, message)."""
```

The runner collects results and exits with code 0 if all pass, 1 otherwise:

```bash
python3 tests/run_scenarios.py --host localhost --port 9000
python3 tests/run_scenarios.py --scenario s04_deadlock_recovery  # run one
python3 tests/run_scenarios.py --scenarios s01,s02,s03            # run subset
python3 tests/run_scenarios.py --verbose                          # show per-step output
```
